The CT changes are of four stages: a. Early stage of ground glass opacities (GGO) in sub-pleural distribution involving mainly lower lobes. b. Progressive stage of multi-lobe distribution with GGO, bilateral consolidation of airspaces (Fig. 1
). c. Peak stage of dense consolidation in almost all cases (Fig. 2
). d. Absorption stage denotes GGO without crazy paving pattern.
